HEADWORD: Plain-laid
<hw>Plain"-laid`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>Consisting of strands twisted together in the ordinary way; <as>as,
a <ex>plain-laid</ex> rope</as>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Cordage</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plainly</ent>⟦br⟧
